questionlist.cardback: are one of the major features of computer programming and we will use them all the time when we are coding. A variable is just a container that stores some information such as a number, an object, or a string.

alert() is a function. A function is something that performs an action. Just like a method, a function can take an argument. The alert() function pops up a dialog box with the string that you pass in as an argument.
toExponential() is called a method. You can think of a method as an action that a number can perform or have taken on it. A method is actually a type of function.
The stuff inside the quotes is called a string. Strings can include letters, punctuation, and even numbers.
